### Describe the unexpected behaviour
If I run SYSTEM STOP MERGES then issue CREATE TABLE then the merge will still run for the newly created table
Not sure if by design or a bug but I think its more intuitive if stop merges prevents merges running for all objects including newly created
### Which ClickHouse versions are affected?
25.10.2.65
### How to reproduce
Clickhouse client
-- If I stop merges THEN create a table then merges still run for the table
SYSTEM STOP MERGES;
drop table foo;
create table foo( x UInt32 ) ENGINE=ReplacingMergeTree() ORDER BY x;
insert into foo values ( 123 );
insert into foo values ( 123 );
insert into foo values ( 123 );
-- Will merge
-- If I create a table THEN stop merges then merges do not run
drop table foo;
create table foo( x UInt32 ) ENGINE=ReplacingMergeTree() ORDER BY x;
SYSTEM STOP MERGES;
insert into foo values ( 123 );
insert into foo values ( 123 );
insert into foo values ( 123 );
-- Will not merge
### Expected behavior
Merges stopped for all tables including newly created
